Defendant Lyronex T Fleming in court with attorney David K Ziemer.  Jay R Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

AS TO COUNT 01:
The Court imposed but stayed 9 months at the House of Correction, with Huber for work and good time; 16 days credit, and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years.

AS TO COUNT 02:
The Court imposed but stayed 3 months at the House of Correction, with Huber for work and good time, consecutive to Count 1, and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years, concurrent to Count 1.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Anger management counseling;
 - No contact with William W.;
 - No contact with co-defendant Tynisha Smith;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay $38.00 joint and several with co-defendant, Tynisha Smith in 14CF460, to William W.; pay DNA surcharge in Count 1 and Count 2, pay the costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit form;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
